div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-24_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-25_"><p class="sc-knuQPt cmQWaw pf-26_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Washing a rug sounds simple, but doing it the wrong way can ruin both your rug and your washing machine. Many people wonder if they can just toss a rug into the washer like a pile of clothes. The truth is, not all rugs are made for that. Some will hold up just fine. Others might shrink, lose their shape, or fall apart.<br><br>In this guide, you'll learn how to tell if your rug is safe to wash, what size can fit in a machine, and the best way to clean it at home without making a mess. Whether you're dealing with everyday dirt or a big spill, we'll walk you through it clearly and simply.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-a455" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dJjagV cQqdEF pf-28_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-kCMLfs khbiTF"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-29_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-30_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-31_ pf-heading-1-h2"><i class="sc-czkhzk fzclRt pf-32_ pf-icon-1 pfa pfa-star pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide pf-hide" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>What Rugs Can Go in the Washing Machine?</h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-33_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-34_"><p class="sc-knuQPt cmQWaw pf-35_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Not every rug can handle a spin in the washer. Before you clean, it helps to know what your rug is made of. Here are the most common types:<br><br>✅ Polyester rugs – These are lightweight, strong, and dry quickly. Many polyester rugs are made for washing machines, which makes them a great choice for busy homes. Learn why polyester is a smart choice for rugs<a href="https://www.lanyspace.com/blogs/rug-inspirations-and-trends/why-lany-space-choose-polyester-to-make-rugs" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(1, 126, 86);"></span></a><a href="https://www.lanyspace.com/blogs/rug-inspirations-and-trends/why-lany-space-choose-polyester-to-make-rugs" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(1, 126, 86);"> </span></a><u><a href="https://www.lanyspace.com/blogs/rug-inspirations-and-trends/why-lany-space-choose-polyester-to-make-rugs" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(1, 126, 86);"></span></a><a href="https://www.lanyspace.com/blogs/rug-inspirations-and-trends/why-lany-space-choose-polyester-to-make-rugs" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(1, 126, 86);"></span></a><a href="https://www.lanyspace.com/blogs/rug-inspirations-and-trends/why-lany-space-choose-polyester-to-make-rugs" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(1, 126, 86);"></span></a><a href="https://www.lanyspace.com/blogs/rug-inspirations-and-trends/why-lany-space-choose-polyester-to-make-rugs" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(1, 126, 86);">i</span></a><a href="https://www.lanyspace.com/blogs/rug-inspirations-and-trends/why-lany-space-choose-polyester-to-make-rugs" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(1, 126, 86);"></span></a><a href="https://www.lanyspace.com/blogs/rug-inspirations-and-trends/why-lany-space-choose-polyester-to-make-rugs" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(1, 126, 86);">n this article</span></a><a href="https://www.lanyspace.com/blogs/rug-inspirations-and-trends/why-lany-space-choose-polyester-to-make-rugs" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(1, 126, 86);"></span></a>.</u><br><br>❌ Wool rugs – Wool is warm and soft, but not washer-friendly. It can shrink or lose shape when soaked in water.<br><br>❌ Rugs with rubber backing – The rubber can crack or melt in the washer, especially in warm water.<br><br>✅ Low-pile synthetic rugs – These are flat, flexible, and often labeled as machine washable. Cold water and a gentle cycle usually work best.<br><br>If you're not sure what your rug is made of, check the label first. A quick look can save you from a big cleaning mistake.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-37_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-38_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h2"><i class="sc-czkhzk fzclRt pf-40_ pf-icon-1 pfa pfa-star pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide pf-hide" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>How to Check if Your Rug is Machine Washable</h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-41_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-42_"><p class="sc-knuQPt cmQWaw pf-43_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Before you wash any rug, take a moment to <strong>check the care label</strong>. Most rugs have a small tag on the back that tells you how to clean it. Look for <strong>machine washable</strong> instructions or a small washing machine icon.<br><br>But not all rugs can go in the washer, even if they look similar. Some are made with extra glue or special backing that can fall apart in water. So don't guess, <strong>always follow the label</strong>.<br><br>If your rug feels too thick or heavy, it may be safer to wash it by hand. Or you can search for a <strong>professional cleaning service near you</strong>. Many laundry shops or dry cleaners offer rug cleaning and can handle sizes or materials that are too tricky at home.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-45_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-46_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-47_ pf-heading-1-h2"><i class="sc-czkhzk fzclRt pf-48_ pf-icon-1 pfa pfa-star pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide pf-hide" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>What Size Rugs Can Fit in a Washer?</h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-49_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-50_"><p class="sc-knuQPt cmQWaw pf-51_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Not all rugs are the same size, and not all washers are built to handle large loads. Here's a quick guide to help you match your rug size with the right washer. This way, you avoid overloading your machine or damaging your rug.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-53_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-54_"><div class="sc-bOhtQk kKaHvF pf-55_ pf-table-default" data-pf-type="Table"><table class="pf-inner-table"><tbody><tr><th class="A1"><span>Rug Size</span></th><th class="B1"><span>Recommended Washer Type</span></th><th class="C1"><span>Washer Capacity (cu. ft.)</span></th><th class="D1"><span>Recommendation</span></th></tr><tr><td class="A2"><span>2′ x 3′</span></td><td class="B2"><span>Standard front-loader</span></td><td class="C2"><span>3.5–4.0 cu. ft.</span></td><td class="D2"><span>✅ Machine washable</span></td></tr><tr><td class="A3"><span>4′ x 6′</span></td><td class="B3"><span>Large front-load washer</span></td><td class="C3"><span>4.2–4.5 cu. ft.</span></td><td class="D3"><span>✅ Roll or fold to fit evenly</span></td></tr><tr><td class="A4"><span>5′ x 7′</span></td><td class="B4"><span>Extra-large front-load washer</span></td><td class="C4"><span>4.5–5.0 cu. ft.</span></td><td class="D4"><span>✅ Fold and balance load</span></td></tr><tr><td class="A5"><span>7′ x 10′</span></td><td class="B5"><span>Industrial washer or laundromat</span></td><td class="C5"><span>Over 5.0 cu. ft.</span></td><td class="D5"><span>⚠️ Laundromat or professional cleaning</span></td></tr><tr><td class="A6"><span>Over 9′ x 12′</span></td><td class="B6"><span>Commercial washer</span></td><td class="C6"><span>Not recommended at home</span></td><td class="D6"><span>⚠️ Professional rug cleaning recommended</span></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-56_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-57_"><p class="sc-knuQPt cmQWaw pf-58_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Quick Tips<br><br>• If the rug feels too bulky, don't force it. Search for professional rug cleaning near you for safer options.<br><br>• Always fold large rugs to help balance the load.<br><br>• Avoid washing very thick or layered rugs at home, even if they fit inside the drum.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-60_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-61_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-62_ pf-heading-1-h2"><i class="sc-czkhzk fzclRt pf-63_ pf-icon-1 pfa pfa-star pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide pf-hide" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>Step-by-Step Guide: How to Wash a Rug in the Washing Machine</h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-64_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-65_"><img title=" How to Wash a Rug in the Washing Machine" alt=" How to Wash a Rug in the Washing Machine(1).webp__PID:d8457af5-8ea0-4507-9e45-e24b21193c3b" src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/64e82ac6986786f5b7a3adb465afea2c_1.webp?v=1748937697&width=2048" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/64e82ac6986786f5b7a3adb465afea2c_1.webp?v=1748937697&width=375 375w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/64e82ac6986786f5b7a3adb465afea2c_1.webp?v=1748937697&width=550 550w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/64e82ac6986786f5b7a3adb465afea2c_1.webp?v=1748937697&width=768 768w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/64e82ac6986786f5b7a3adb465afea2c_1.webp?v=1748937697&width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/64e82ac6986786f5b7a3adb465afea2c_1.webp?v=1748937697&width=1280 1280w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/64e82ac6986786f5b7a3adb465afea2c_1.webp?v=1748937697&width=1440 1440w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/64e82ac6986786f5b7a3adb465afea2c_1.webp?v=1748937697&width=1680 1680w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/64e82ac6986786f5b7a3adb465afea2c_1.webp?v=1748937697&width=1800 1800w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/64e82ac6986786f5b7a3adb465afea2c_1.webp?v=1748937697&width=1920 1920w,https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0619/2998/0042/files/64e82ac6986786f5b7a3adb465afea2c_1.webp?v=1748937697&width=2048 2048w" fetchPriority="low" decoding="async" loading="lazy" style="--pf-image-ratio:1.5" width="1536" height="1024" sizes="75vw" data-pf-type="Image4" class="sc-dWZrec jpHayX pf-66_" store="[object Object]"/></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-67_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-68_"><p class="sc-knuQPt cmQWaw pf-69_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Washing a rug at home is easier than it sounds, as long as you follow the right steps.<br><br><em><strong>Step 1:</strong></em>&nbsp;Shake off loose debris like dust, hair, or crumbs before you begin. This keeps your washer cleaner and helps your rug wash more evenly.<br><br><strong><em>Step 2:</em></strong> Pre-treat any stains using a mix of cold water and mild detergent. Gently blot the spot with a cloth, especially for spills or sticky marks.<br><br><em><strong>Step 3:</strong></em> Fold the rug carefully so it fits well in the drum. This helps balance the load and keeps your washer from shaking too much.<br><br><em><strong>Step 4:&nbsp;</strong></em>Use cold water and a gentle detergent to protect the rug fibers and colors.<br><br><strong><em>Step 5:&nbsp;</em></strong>Select the gentle cycle on your machine. Avoid fast spins or heavy-duty settings.<br><br><em><strong>Step 6:</strong></em>&nbsp;Air dry the rug flat. Skip the dryer, and keep it out of direct sunlight to prevent fading.<br><br>Want to keep your rug looking fresh for longer? Take a look at our <a href="https://www.lanyspace.com/blogs/rug-inspirations-and-trends/lany-space-rug-care-guide-how-to-clean-and-care-for-your-polyester-rug-the-easy-way" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(1, 126, 86);"><u>rug care tips</u></span></a> for more simple ways to clean and protect it.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-71_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-72_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-73_">Air-Drying vs Machine Drying: What's Safer for Rugs?</h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-75_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-76_"><p class="sc-knuQPt cmQWaw pf-77_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">After washing your rug, drying it the right way helps protect both its shape and color. Most experts still recommend <em><strong>air drying</strong></em> as the safest method. Even rugs made from polyester, which is known for being quick-drying and durable, can be affected by high heat. The backing may soften or warp, and the edges may curl or shrink. Direct heat can also cause printed colors to fade, especially on patterned rugs.<br><br>To air dry your rug, first press out extra water with a clean, dry towel. Then lay the rug flat in a shaded area with good airflow. Avoid hanging it, since that may stretch the edges or cause creases. Keep it away from radiators, heaters, and direct sunlight. These small steps may take a little more time, but they help your rug stay soft, flat, and in good shape for longer.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-79_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-80_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-81_">Smart Tips to Make Your Rug Last Longer</h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-83_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-84_"><p class="sc-knuQPt cmQWaw pf-85_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">With just a few simple habits, you can keep your rug looking fresh and feeling soft for years. Here's how to take better care of it:<br><br><strong>Avoid over-washing:</strong> Too much washing wears out the backing and fades the colors. Stick to once every 1 to 2 months unless there's a spill. For daily dust or pet hair, vacuuming is enough.<br><br><strong>Rotate your rug:</strong> Changing the rug's position helps it wear evenly. In high-traffic areas, one side may fade or flatten faster. Rotating your rug every few weeks keeps it looking balanced and fresh.<br><br><strong>Spot clean immediately:</strong> Small stains are easier to remove when treated early. Use a soft cloth and mild soap to dab, not rub. Waiting too long can cause stains to set into the fibers.<br><br><strong>Keep soak time short:</strong> Rugs don't need long baths to get clean. If hand-washing, rinse quickly after cleaning. Soaking too long can loosen the weave, dull the finish, and damage the shape.<br><br>These small habits take only minutes, but they can help your rug stay bright, soft, and looking like new for years.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-87_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-88_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kRRxPL kSaugo pf-89_ pf-heading-1-h2"><i class="sc-czkhzk fzclRt pf-90_ pf-icon-1 pfa pfa-star pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide pf-hide" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>Final Thought</h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-91_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bkSTSn hpQOMO pf-92_"><p class="sc-knuQPt cmQWaw pf-93_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">A rug should feel as easy to care for as it is to enjoy. When life gets messy with muddy shoes, spilled snacks, or an excited pet racing through the room, you deserve a rug that can handle it all without stress. With the right cleaning steps and a little attention to timing, your rug can stay soft, fresh, and full of color for years to come. If you're ready for something that keeps up with real living and still looks beautiful, explore our <a href="https://www.lanyspace.com/collections/shop-all" target="_self"><span style="color: rgb(1, 126, 86);"><u>washable polyester rug collection</u></span></a> and find the one that fits your space and your rhythm.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-95_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="